/F2 14.00 Tf 54.00 738.00 Td (22. What is IVFFlat?) Tj
/F1 10.00 Tf 54.00 714.10 Td (IVFFlat means Inverted File Flat. It clusters vectors into groups. At query time, it searches) Tj
/F1 10.00 Tf 54.00 700.60 Td (only the nearest clusters instead of all vectors.) Tj
/F1 9.50 Tf 66.00 681.10 Td (- Can be fast on large datasets.) Tj
/F1 9.50 Tf 66.00 665.27 Td (- Can be memory-efficient.) Tj
/F1 9.50 Tf 66.00 649.45 Td (- Requires representative data before index creation.) Tj
/F1 9.50 Tf 66.00 633.62 Td (- Needs tuning such as list count and probes.) Tj
/F1 9.50 Tf 66.00 617.80 Td (- Recall can suffer if the clustering or probe settings are not tuned well.) Tj
/F2 14.00 Tf 54.00 593.97 Td (23. Why use HNSW instead of IVFFlat in this project?) Tj
/F1 10.00 Tf 54.00 570.07 Td (HNSW fits this project because documents are uploaded over time and chunks are added) Tj
/F1 10.00 Tf 54.00 556.57 Td (incrementally. It gives strong semantic retrieval quality without requiring a separate training) Tj
/F1 10.00 Tf 54.00 543.07 Td (step.) Tj
/F1 10.00 Tf 54.00 523.57 Td (IVFFlat can be excellent, but it is more sensitive to setup. You need enough representative) Tj
/F1 10.00 Tf 54.00 510.07 Td (vectors, a good number of lists, and tuned probes. For a learning-focused RAG app, HNSW is) Tj
/F1 10.00 Tf 54.00 496.57 Td (simpler and usually a better default.) Tj
/F2 14.00 Tf 54.00 469.07 Td (24. What are the main retrieval tradeoffs in this project?) Tj
/F1 9.50 Tf 66.00 445.17 Td (- Semantic search handles paraphrases and meaning, but can miss exact IDs, function names,) Tj
/F1 9.50 Tf 66.00 432.35 Td (acronyms, or error codes.) Tj
/F1 9.50 Tf 66.00 416.52 Td (- Keyword search handles exact terms well, but can miss relevant chunks when the user phrases the) Tj
/F1 9.50 Tf 66.00 403.70 Td (idea differently.) Tj
